In England, in the seven days to 30 November, there were 260,894 new confirmed cases (461.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 November, there were 248,249 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (12,645 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 05 December is 8,877,883 (15,699.1 cases per 100,000 population).
